ĘIn Loving Memory of Barbara Alice Harper
1934 2015
She was passionate about her gardening and enjoyed sharing
her love of nature and wildlife with family and friends"ź
Ęin Loving and lasting memory of my precious angel
BALAZS MIKLOS TOTH
(7.1.1985 27.11 2013)
He loved Battersea Park
As did his mother Zsuzsanna (d31.12.2011)
Gordon"Č
ęMICHAEL HORSMAN 1932-2009
Architect of Ralph West Hall, Albert Bridge Road
Built 1962, demolished 2000
No hell below, no heaven above
Live life now and act with love"▓
»DAVID BUCKNELL (DJB) 1939 - 2004
Bon viveur, raconteur, tin collector extraordinaire
was born to retire and went to Paradise by way of
Kensal Green (and a hostelry or two!)"│
░Stranger Stop Here and Rest Your Thoughts on
LOVELY LISA GRAYLEY
Mum to Pretty Lottie, Sweetheart to Paul and Beautiful Friend to
Those of Us Who Knew Her "Sweet Dreams Sis""Ş
ÁEve Louise Boundy
15th July 2014
If ever there is tomorrow when we're not together...there is something you
must always remember. You are braver than you believe, stronger than you
seem and smarter than you think. But the most important thing is
even if we're apart... I'll always be with you
A.A. Milne"╣
ÂTHOMAS BRAWLEY 03/08/1919 to 31/12/2009
Beloved husband, father & grandfather. Tommy liked to walk daily
round the Park to observe the seasonal changes unfolding.
We enjoyed many happy family hours in his special place.
A wonderful husband and father with great wit and intelligence
he loved his family dearly and we miss him so much.
AGNES BRAWLEY
20th September 1923 to 22nd of March 2013
Much loved Wife, Mother and Grandmother"ż
╗Mary Zammit
2nd May 1923 - 26th November 2014
Your life was a blessing your memory treasured every day
An amazing Mum, Nan & Great Grandma
Peter Paul Zammit
7th May 1922 - 10th May 2012
A wonderful dad, grandad & great grandad. In memory of all
the happy times spent here in this park with your grandchildren"┐
