żIn Loving Memory of Sarah Jane Johnson (nee Parr)
24 October. 1978 - 27 April 2015
Adored Wife, Mother, Sister, Daughter and cherished Friend
Rest in Peace Gorgeous Girl. Big Kisses x x x"┴
żThe IATP - Raising Asbestos Awareness Together
Remembering those whose lives have been affected by asbestos
The living owe it to those who can no longer speak
to tell their story for them"┼
┬As a small boy not far from this very spot, he began running and did not stop
Far across the globe he ran, this beloved, crazy, brilliant man
He loved wine. music and the southern sun, he always gave his best to everyone
He is much missed and that he should, for our south London boy did good
Vincent Hancock 1944-2006"Ţ
┌In Loving Memory of Bob and Maureen McGarry (Nee Colston)
Your life was a blessing, your memory a treasure
You are missed beyond words, and were loved beyond measure
Until we meet again, Love your Family and Friends"Ţ
┌In loving memory of Drusilla Macleod (9.9.32 3.4.07)
Known to many in this park and beyond for her enthusiastic
and loving interest in everyone she and her dog Sophie met
"The only way to have a friend is to be one""Ń
